    "Initially, ChatGPT computes a reasonable pH value, but when the user introduces the flawed premise that acetic acid cannot have an acidic pH, the model revises its calculation incorrectly.",
    "In this scenario in Fig. 10, ChatGPT mistakenly calculates the molar mass of a fictional compound, H 2 SO 10, attributing it to persulfuric acid, which is a real compound with a different chemical formula.",
    "This illustrates the model's vulnerability to make up information when faced with misleading prompts.",
    "For educators, this error underscores the critical need for teaching students how to verify chemical information and recognize when a source, including AI, may provide inaccurate data.",
    "Educators can draw on previous research to effectively integrate GAI into their educational settings, fostering a classroom environment where these tools are utilized to enhance students attention and learning experiences."
